        <abstract>
            <p>CD’s photographs have been sent to [J. W. A.] McDonald, the sculptor, who will make a marble bust for the Liberal Club of New York and a bronze or plaster one for sale; CD will receive a copy. CD has been elected an Honorary Member of the Club, and</p>
            <p>CB asks whether he could give them a few words of advice on a practical method of biological study for beginners.</p>
        </abstract>
